# ALAMS Pilot Deployment Guide
## 10-Machine Lab Rollout — Operational Runbook

> **Target:** Deploy ALAMS to 10 physical Windows lab computers and validate a full classroom session.
> **Goal:** ≥95% login success rate · QR unlock ≤10s · Zero undetected bypasses

---

## Pre-Deployment Checklist

### Server Environment

| Task | Command | Status |
|---|---|---|
| PostgreSQL running | `Get-Service postgresql*` | `[ ]` |
| Database schema synced | `cd server && npx prisma db push` | `[ ]` |
| Seed admin account | `npm run prisma:seed` | `[ ]` |
| Server reachable | `curl http://localhost:5000/health` | `[ ]` |
| Web dashboard accessible | Open `http://SERVER_IP:3000/admin/login` | `[ ]` |
| Admin login works | `ADMIN01` / `admin123` | `[ ]` |

> [!IMPORTANT]
> Replace `localhost` with the server machine's actual LAN IP in all workstation `config.json` files and in `web/.env.local` (`NEXT_PUBLIC_API_URL=http://SERVER_LAN_IP:5000`).

### Software Ready on Each PC

| File | Location |
|---|---|
| `AlamsClient.exe` | `C:\Program Files\ALAMS\` |
| `AlamsWatchdog.exe` | `C:\Program Files\ALAMS\` |
| `AlamsInstaller.msi` | Run before enrollment |

---

## Per-Workstation Enrollment (Repeat × 10)

### Step 1: Run MSI Installer
```powershell
# On each lab PC — run as Administrator
msiexec /i AlamsInstaller.msi /quiet
```
This installs binaries to `C:\Program Files\ALAMS\` and registers + starts `AlamsWatchdog` service.

### Step 2: Verify Watchdog Service
```powershell
Get-Service AlamsWatchdog
# Expected: Status = Running, StartType = Automatic
```

### Step 3: Run Shell Enrollment
```powershell
# Run as Administrator, while logged in as the STUDENT user account
Set-ExecutionPolicy Bypass -Scope Process -Force
.\EnrollShell.ps1
```

### Step 4: First-Launch Registration
1. Log out of admin account.
2. Log in as the student user — ALAMS lock screen appears instead of desktop.
3. Client auto-registers with server (PENDING state shown on screen).
4. On Admin Dashboard → Live Monitor → Pending Enrollments section:
   - Enter PC Number: `PC-01` through `PC-10`
   - Select Lab Zone: e.g. "Turing Computing Lab"
   - Click **Approve & Lock**
5. Client screen should transition from PENDING → QR lock screen within seconds.

### Step 5: Stick Physical QR Label
- After approval, print a static label with the **PC Number** and stick it visibly on the monitor bezel.
- The dynamic QR displayed on-screen is what students scan — do **not** print or laminate the dynamic QR.

---

## Validation Tests (Per Machine)

### TEST-01: QR Authentication Flow

| Step | Action | Expected Result | Pass? |
|---|---|---|---|
| 1 | Student enters Enrollment Number | Name is displayed on lock screen | `[ ]` |
| 2 | Student clicks "Get QR Code" | Dynamic QR renders with 60s countdown | `[ ]` |
| 3 | Student scans QR on mobile | Mobile verification page opens | `[ ]` |
| 4 | Student taps "Authorize Access" | Desktop unlocks within 10 seconds | `[ ]` |
| 5 | Session appears in Admin Dashboard | Correct student, PC, time shown | `[ ]` |
| 6 | Faculty Attendance tab shows student | Name + enrollment visible | `[ ]` |

### TEST-02: Watchdog Bypass Enforcement

> [!CAUTION]
> Perform this test ONLY with admin credentials. Do not perform on machines during class.

| Step | Action | Expected Result | Pass? |
|---|---|---|---|
| 1 | Open Task Manager as admin | - | `[ ]` |
| 2 | Kill `AlamsClient.exe` | Windows should immediately log off the user | `[ ]` |
| 3 | Check Admin Dashboard → Security Audits | Critical alert: `watchdog_kill` should appear | `[ ]` |
| 4 | Log back in | ALAMS lock screen loads (not desktop) | `[ ]` |

### TEST-03: Shell Replacement Verification

| Step | Action | Expected Result | Pass? |
|---|---|---|---|
| 1 | Log in as student user | ALAMS Client loads, NOT desktop | `[ ]` |
| 2 | Press `Ctrl+Alt+Del` | Windows Security screen (normal) | `[ ]` |
| 3 | Press `Win`, `Win+D`, `Win+E` | No response — desktop locked | `[ ]` |
| 4 | Unlock with QR | Explorer.exe starts, desktop accessible | `[ ]` |
| 5 | Log out from session toolbar | Lock screen returns | `[ ]` |

### TEST-04: Offline Recovery (PIN Fallback)

| Step | Action | Expected Result | Pass? |
|---|---|---|---|
| 1 | Disconnect LAN cable | Status indicator goes OFFLINE (red) | `[ ]` |
| 2 | Student enters Enrollment + PIN | Offline PIN validation succeeds | `[ ]` |
| 3 | Reconnect LAN cable | WebSocket reconnects, session syncs | `[ ]` |
| 4 | Session appears in audit log | Method: `PIN_FALLBACK` recorded | `[ ]` |

### TEST-05: Admin Remote Lock/Unlock

| Step | Action | Expected Result | Pass? |
|---|---|---|---|
| 1 | Identify active session in dashboard | Student shown as IN_USE | `[ ]` |
| 2 | Click Remote Lock on PC card | Session terminates, PC locks instantly | `[ ]` |
| 3 | Click Remote Unlock on a locked PC | Admin OVERRIDE session opens | `[ ]` |

---

## Network Requirements

```
Lab PCs     ─── LAN ───> Server (TCP 5000 + WS)
Mobile       ─── WiFi ──> Server (TCP 3000 / public URL)
Admin Browser ─── LAN ──> Server (TCP 3000)

Firewall: Allow inbound TCP 5000 and 3000 on server machine.
```

---

## Performance Targets

Record these metrics after running the validation session:

| Metric | Target | Measured |
|---|---|---|
| Login Success Rate | ≥ 95% | `_____` |
| QR Unlock Time (avg) | ≤ 10 seconds | `_____` |
| PIN Fallback Time (avg) | ≤ 5 seconds | `_____` |
| Watchdog Response Time | ≤ 3 seconds to logoff | `_____` |
| PCs Online (steady state) | 10/10 | `_____` |
| Watchdog Active (ratio) | 10/10 | `_____` |
| Bypasses Blocked | 0 undetected | `_____` |

---

## Rollback Procedure

If any workstation needs to be restored to normal Windows shell:

```powershell
# Run as Administrator on affected workstation
$regPath = "HKCU:\Software\Microsoft\Windows NT\CurrentVersion\Winlogon"
Remove-ItemProperty -Path $regPath -Name "Shell" -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue
# OR restore backup:
$backup = Get-Content "C:\ProgramData\ALAMS\shell_backup.txt"
Set-ItemProperty -Path $regPath -Name "Shell" -Value $backup
Write-Host "Shell restored to: $backup"
```

```powershell
# Stop and disable Watchdog service
Stop-Service AlamsWatchdog -Force
Set-Service AlamsWatchdog -StartupType Disabled
```

---

## Post-Pilot Report

After completing validation, capture screenshots of:
1. **Pilot Analytics tab** — login success %, avg unlock time, hourly distribution
2. **Session Audit tab** — full list of test sessions with verification methods
3. **Security Audits tab** — watchdog_kill entries from bypass tests
4. **Faculty Attendance tab** — roster from the test session

Submit the captured data with this runbook as the pilot feedback report.
